UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842669390078R
AB  - We derive simple closed-form expressions for European options on coupon bonds using the general equilibrium term-structure framework of Cox, Ingersoll, and Ross The properties of these options are very different from those implied by the Black-Scholes model For example, bond call and put values can move in the same direction as the value of the underlying bond changes This has important implications for hedging interest-rate risk with bond options. Furthermore, bond option values can be decreasing functions of interest-rate volatility as well as their time to expiration We also examine the properties of American bond options
